@NODE "eyecandy" "Customizing the look"

By default this program looks for a dir in env: ...
env:Scalos/Modules/Information.module/

in this dir can exist the following things...

Icons....

 Wflag.info
 Sflag.info
 Rflag.info
 Pflag.info
 Hflag.info
 Eflag.info
 Dflag.info
 Aflag.info

Images...

 Rename
 Sort
 Add New
 ToolTypes
 Main Info
 Save
 Cancel
 Delete

If the icons are present they will be used as the images for the
protection flag gadgets. they can be normal or Newicons and use
the MUI Icon.mcc class to load.

If the images are present they will be used as eye candy for the gadgets.
they can be any format your datatypes.library can load but should not
be a larger height than the gadgets or they will be cropped.

Supplied is a "Themes" dir.
In this dir are the following dirs...

       Topaz ; a glowicon set of protection flags
       Large ; a large glowicon set of protection flags
Large_Future ; another large glowicon set of protection flags

     Buttons ; a set of button images

just copy the contents of the Buttons dir and one of the icon sets to
env:Scalos/Modules/Information.module/

A different dir can be used by changing the "IconDir" setting in the
Information.ini file.

The Information.ini file sits in ENV(ARC):Scalos/ and will be automaticaly
created if it does not exist


@ENDNODE

@NODE "ini" "settings"

Soon i will make a gui for editing these settings.

but for now...

This is a copy of the default settings
file created if not allready there...

@{fg highlight}
[General]
StackList=0,1024,4096,8192,16384,32768.65536
[Protection Images]
IconDir=env:Scalos/Modules/Information.module
ShowIconFrames=1
ShowMainFrame=0
[ToolType Popups]
DoNotWait=DONOTWAIT
Shell Console=Window=CON:////Output/close/wait
ARexx Console=CON=CON:////Output/close/wait
[Comment Popups]
My Email=bsteers@ukonline.co.uk
Made By Me=Written by Bruce Steers
[DefTool Popups]
Multiview=SYS:Utilities/Multiview
IconX=C:IconX
RX=SYS:Rexxc/rx
Diskcopy=SYS:System/DiskCopy
@{fg text}

Explanation:

[General]
StackList= A list of values to display in the stack popup list
Default: 0,1024,4096,8192,16384,32768.65536

[Protection Images]
IconDir=Dir to look for the images to @{"customise the gui" LINK "eyecandy"}
Default: env:Scalos/Modules/Information.module

ShowIconFrames=1 or 0, show frame around each protecion image.
Default: 1
ShowMainFrame=1 or 0, show main frame around protecion images.
Default: 0

The next 3 groups define the popup lists for the relevant gadget.
Use ItemName=Text
and DO NOT use = in the name
Here are the defaults...

[ToolType Popups]
DoNotWait=DONOTWAIT
Shell Console=Window=CON:////Output/close/wait
ARexx Console=CON=CON:////Output/close/wait

[Comment Popups]
My Email=bsteers@ukonline.co.uk
Made By Me=Written by Bruce Steers

[DefTool Popups]
Multiview=SYS:Utilities/Multiview
IconX=C:IconX
RX=SYS:Rexxc/rx
Diskcopy=SYS:System/DiskCopy


@ENDNODE

@NODE "bugs" dem damn bugs

Known Bugs...

1st load enforcer hit:
When you first run the module and no Infomation.ini
file exists it creates an enforcer hit.

This is a bug in the amigaini.library.
This does not happen again as the file has been created.

As i also wrote the amigaini.library i am
currently looking into this bug.

---

No icon does not give Deficon image:
If no icon exists it uses only disk/tool/project
images and not the deficons ones.

this may be fixed in the future.

---

@ENDNODE


@NODE "use" "Usage"

General Usage.

Not much to say really as it works a lot like
the original scalos information.module

except for popup gadgets on all the strings.

Click the tooltypes button to go to the tooltypes page.
Click it again to go back to the Main Info page.


@ENDNODE

